# isEnabled

**Instance Property**

A property you use to toggle enabling the configuration.

## Declaration

```swift
var isEnabled: Bool { get set }
```

## Discussion

The framework sets this value to NO when your app saves a configuration that overlaps with this configuration. This overlap occurs when a new [doc://com.apple.networkextension/documentation/NetworkExtension/NEAppPushManager] saves a configuration with a [doc://com.apple.networkextension/documentation/NetworkExtension/NEAppPushManager/matchSSIDs] list that contains an SSID which is also a member of this manager’s SSID list.

## Inspecting manager properties

- **isActive**: A Boolean value that indicates whether a configuration is in use.
- **localizedDescription**: A string that contains the localized description of the app push manager.
